Beijing PM2.5 Data Data Set

  • 2010 1 1 2014 12 31 , PM2.5 .

Description of variables

  • No: row number

  • year: year of data in this row

  • month: month of data in this row

  • day: day of data in this row

  • hour: hour of data in this row

  • pm2.5: PM2.5 concentration (ug/m^3)

  • DEWP: Dew Point ()

  • TEMP: Temperature ()

  • PRES: Pressure (hPa)

  • cbwd: Combined wind direction

  • Iws: Cumulated wind speed (m/s)

  • Is: Cumulated hours of snow

  • Ir: Cumulated hours of rain

- No, year, month, day, hour, cbwd , (NA) .

4 probit link

  • : \(\Phi^{-1}(p_{i})=\beta_{0}+\beta_{1}x_{1i}+\beta_{2}x_{2i}+\beta_{3}x_{3i}+\beta_{4}x_{4i}+\beta_{5}x_{5i}+\beta_{6}x_{6i}\)
  • \(\Phi\) : CDF of \(N(0,1^2)\)
model2 <- glm(pm.bin ~ DEWP+TEMP+PRES+Iws+Is+Ir, family=binomial(link = probit), data=PRSA)

7 kernel smoothing regression, local linear regression

  • 3~6 DEWP(Dew Point) pm2.5 kernel smoothing regression . Gaussian kernel Nadaraya-Watson kernel smoothing regression local linear regression . kernel .
library(KernSmooth)
## Warning:  'KernSmooth' R  4.1.3 
## KernSmooth 2.23 loaded
## Copyright M. P. Wand 1997-2009
with(PRSA, {
    plot(DEWP, pm2.5, main="NW vs LL")
    lines(ksmooth(DEWP, pm2.5, kernel="normal", bandwidth=0.5), col='red', lwd=2)
    lines(locpoly(DEWP, pm2.5, kernel="normal", bandwidth=0.5), col='blue', lwd=2)
    legend("topleft", legend=c("NW","LL"), col=c('red','blue'), lwd=c(2,2))
})
